column1: #FORMAT=WebAnno TSV 3.2

#T_RL=webanno.custom.Coref|type|BT_webanno.custom.Referent
#Text=Wow .
#Text=Whoa .
#Text=That is some group of people .
#Text=Thousands .
#Text=So nice , thank you very much .
#Text=That 's really nice .
#Text=Thank you .
#Text=It 's great to be at Trump Tower .
#Text=It 's great to be in a wonderful city , New York .
#Text=And it 's an honor to have everybody here .
#Text=This is beyond anybody 's expectations .
#Text=There 's been no crowd like this .
#Text=And , I can tell you , some of the candidates , they went in .
#Text=They did n't know the air - conditioner did n't work .
#Text=They sweated like dogs .
#Text=They did n't know the room was too big , because they did n't have anybody there .
#Text=How are they going to beat ISIS ?
#Text=I do n't think it 's gon na happen .
#Text=Our country is in serious trouble .
#Text=We do n't have victories anymore .
#Text=We used to have victories , but we do n't have them .
#Text=When was the last time anybody saw us beating , let 's say , China in a trade deal ?
#Text=They kill us .
#Text=I beat China all the time .
#Text=All the time .
#Text=We want Trump .
#Text=We want Trump .
#Text=When did we beat Japan at anything ?
#Text=They send their cars over by the millions , and what do we do ?
#Text=When was the last time you saw a Chevrolet in Tokyo ?
#Text=It does n't exist , folks .
#Text=They beat us all the time .
#Text=When do we beat Mexico at the border ?
#Text=They 're laughing at us , at our stupidity .
#Text=And now they are beating us economically .
#Text=They are not our friend , believe me .
#Text=But they 're killing us economically .
#Text=The U.S. has become a dumping ground for everybody else 's problems .
#Text=Thank you .
#Text=It 's true , and these are the best and the finest .
#Text=When Mexico sends its people , they 're not sending their best .
#Text=They 're not sending you .
#Text=They 're not sending you .
#Text=They 're sending people that have lots of problems , and they 're bringing those problems with us .
#Text=They 're bringing drugs .
#Text=They 're bringing crime .
#Text=They 're rapists .
#Text=And some , I assume , are good people .
#Text=But I speak to border guards and they tell us what we 're getting .
#Text=And it only makes common sense .
#Text=It only makes common sense .
#Text=They 're sending us not the right people .
#Text=It 's coming from more than Mexico .
#Text=It 's coming from all over South and Latin America , and it 's coming probably — probably — from the Middle East .
#Text=But we do n't know .
#Text=Because we have no protection and we have no competence , we do n't know what 's happening .
#Text=And it 's got to stop and it 's got to stop fast .
#Text=Islamic terrorism is eating up large portions of the Middle East .
#Text=They 've become rich .
#Text=I 'm in competition with them .
#Text=They just built a hotel in Syria .
#Text=Can you believe this ?
#Text=They built a hotel .
#Text=When I have to build a hotel , I pay interest .
#Text=They do n't have to pay interest , because they took the oil that , when we left Iraq , I said we should 've taken .
#Text=So now ISIS has the oil , and what they do n't have , Iran has .

#Text=And in 19 — and I will tell you this , and I said it very strongly , years ago , I said — and I love the military , and I want to have the strongest military that we 've ever had , and we need it more now than ever .
#Text=But I said , " Do n't hit Iraq , " because you 're going to totally destabilize the Middle East .
#Text=Iran is going to take over the Middle East , Iran and somebody else will get the oil , and it turned out that Iran is now taking over Iraq .
#Text=Think of it .
#Text=Iran is taking over Iraq , and they 're taking it over big league .
#Text=We spent $ 2 trillion in Iraq , $ 2 trillion .
#Text=We lost thousands of lives , thousands in Iraq .
#Text=We have wounded soldiers , who I love , I love — they 're great — all over the place , thousands and thousands of wounded soldiers .
#Text=And we have nothing .
#Text=We ca n't even go there .
#Text=We have nothing .
#Text=And every time we give Iraq equipment , the first time a bullet goes off in the air , they leave it .
#Text=Last week , I read 2,300 Humvees — these are big vehicles — were left behind for the enemy .
#Text=You would say maybe two , maybe four ?
#Text=2,300 sophisticated vehicles , they ran , and the enemy took them .
#Text=We need Trump now .
#Text=You 're right .
#Text=We need Trump now .
#Text=Last quarter , it was just announced our gross domestic product — a sign of strength , right ?
#Text=But not for us .
#Text=It was below zero .
#Text=Whoever heard of this ?
#Text=It 's never below zero .
#Text=Our labor participation rate was the worst since 1978 .
#Text=But think of it , GDP below zero , horrible labor participation rate .
#Text=And our real unemployment is anywhere from 18 to 20 percent .
#Text=Do n't believe the 5.6 .
#Text=Do n't believe it .
#Text=That 's right .
#Text=A lot of people up there ca n't get jobs .
#Text=They ca n't get jobs , because there are no jobs , because China has our jobs and Mexico has our jobs .
#Text=They all have jobs .
#Text=But the real number , the real number is anywhere from 18 to 19 and maybe even 21 percent , and nobody talks about it , because it 's a statistic that 's full of nonsense .
#Text=We want Trump now .
#Text=Our enemies are getting stronger and stronger by the way , and we as a country are getting weaker .
#Text=Even our nuclear arsenal does n't work .
#Text=It came out recently they have equipment that is 30 years old .
#Text=They do n't know if it worked .
#Text=And I thought it was horrible when it was broadcast on television , because boy , does that send signals to Putin and all of the other people that look at us and they say ,
#Text=" That is a group of people , and that is a nation that truly has no clue .
